                    "company": "MDF | Empowering People, Creating Impact",
                    "description": "Managing MDF\u2019s operations in the Eastern and Southern African region, including client relations, programme design and management, and implementation and oversight of training and advisory assignments with public and private sector clients.  Bas managed an international and interdisciplinary network of 20 highly qualified consultants to deliver tailor-made training for groups of 8-60 participants, undertook organisational development for a range of public and private organisations and performed other consultancy assignments such as evaluation studies, development of monitoring plans and management systems e.g. HR manuals. \n\nBas set business strategy and budgets, succeeding in building the organisation into a commercially sustainable business, going from providing 2 consulting assignment and 50 training courses in 5 countries in 2009 to 40 assignments and 100 training courses being delivered across 14 countries from Sudan to Namibia, with a solid base in Tanzania. \nThrough this role, Bas worked with donor agencies including GIZ, USAID, UNFPA, UNDP, ILO, FAO, FINAID, IrishAid, NUFFIC, MinBuZa Foreign Affairs, ORIO infrastructure for development fund, Dutch Embassies in Nairobi and Addis Ababa, and SDC; developed MDF\u2019s reputation as leading providing of training to NGOs in the region, and developed new lines of work responding directly to the needs of the business. \n\nAs a Qualified trainer and facilitator, Bas was responsible for designing and facilitating training courses in Outcome Mapping; RBM; M&E; Advocacy and Policy Influencing; Business Development Services and Financial Management. \nAs consultant, Bas actively delivered organisational development building and advisory services to CSOs and NGOs in the East and Southern Africa region, with a focus on M&E, RBM, organisational assessment, change management and strategic development.",
